"'''Tall Tales'''" is an eight-page comic appearing in ''[[Star Wars Tales 11]]'' and collected in ''[[Star Wars Tales Volume 3]]''.

==Plot summary==
In a cantina, five patrons play cards and share stories about their own takes on the events of the [[original trilogy]], none of them entirely accurate or truthful. They tell tales of how [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] attacked a squad of [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] in the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Mos Eisley cantina]] and stopped them from taking [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] to his father, the [[Palpatine/Legends|Emperor]], how [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], after murdering [[Greedo/Legends|Greedo]] in cold blood, helped [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]], and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] burn down a cantina full of women and children in their escape from [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]], and how [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia]] stole the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] from the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]]. As their game draws to a close, a [[Morseerian/Legends|Morseerian]] working for [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]] attempts to kidnap one of the players, the son of [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Amara (Human)|Amara]]. Another player, a cloaked stranger, quickly springs into action and kills him with a single shot. As he leaves, the rogueish grin he flashes shows him to be none other than Han Solo. Behind him, within the cantina, the other players are already spinning their own tall tales about what they just saw...

